div.div: Sekai Saikou no Ansatsusha, Isekai Kizoku ni Tensei suru
Action, Adventure, Drama, Fantasy, Mystery, Romance

The world's number one assassin has been reincarnated as the eldest son of a family of aristocrat assassins. In exchange for being reincarnated in another world, a goddess has imposed upon him one condition. "Kill the Hero who is prophesied to destroy the world."
This was to be the mission in his new life. The synergistic effect of the vast knowledge and experience he gained that made all manner of assassinations possible in the modern world, and the secret techniques and magic of the fantasy world's most powerful family of assassins turn him into the greatest assassin of all time.
(Source: Crunchyroll)

A boy fights... for "the right death." Hardship, regret, shame: the negative feelings that humans feel become Curses that lurk in our everyday lives. The Curses run rampant throughout the world, capable of leading people to terrible misfortune and even death. What's more, the Curses can only be exorcised by another Curse. Itadori Yuji is a boy with tremendous physical strength, though he lives a completely ordinary high school life. One day, to save a friend who has been attacked by Curses, he eats the finger of the Double-Faced Specter, taking the Curse into his own soul. From then on, he shares one body with the Double-Faced Specter. Guided by the most powerful of sorcerers, Gojou Satoru, Itadori is admitted to the Tokyo Metropolitan Technical High School of Sorcery, an organization that fights the Curses... and thus begins the heroic tale of a boy who became a Curse to exorcise a Curse, a life from which he could never turn back. (Source: Crunchyroll) Note: The first episode received an early web premiere on September 19th, 2020. The regular TV broadcast started on October 3rd, 2020.

At school, Kyouko Hori is known for being smart, attractive, and popular. On the other hand, her classmate, the boring, gloomy Izumi Miyamura tends to get painted as a "loser fanboy." But when a liberally pierced and tattooed (not to mention downright gorgeous) Miyamura appears unexpectedly on the doorstep of secretly plain-Jane homebody Hori, these two similarly dissimilar teenagers discover that there are multiple sides to every story...and person! (Source: Yen Press) Note: Includes 20 extra chapters.
Monster ga Afureru Sekai ni Natta kedo, Tayoreru Neko ga Iru kara Daijoubu desu.

On her way home from shopping for dinner, Kujo Ayame, a new member of society who lives with her tortoiseshell cat, Haru, gets caught up in the drastic changes in the world. The changed cityscape, monsters attacking people, and people awakening to their skills....
In the turmoil, Ayame and Haru accidentally succeed in defeating a giant monster, and at that moment, a voice echoes in their heads. ["Kujo Ayame's LV has increased from 1 to 10"]
["Confirming the first named monster defeat in Chaos Frontier Acquired the bonus skill "Search"]
With that as a trigger, Ayame made full use of her search skill to survive in a overflowing with monsters.
Moreover, Ayame is not the only one who has awakened to this skill; her cat Haru has also acquired the useful cheat-level skill "Conversion"!
(Source: GA Novels, translated)
